The course gives an overview of the main varieties of English spoken in North America, the Caribbean area, Australia, New Zealand, Africa, South-East Asia and South Asia, focussing on their emergence and linguistic features. The course also touches upon English-based pidgins and creoles.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of the main varieties of English spoken in North America, the Caribbean area, Australia, New Zealand, Africa, South-East Asia and South Asia, focussing on their emergence and linguistic features. The course also touches upon English-based pidgins and creoles.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of the course, the students will - have an understanding of how and why English became distributed in the world;  - know general phonetic, grammatical and lexical features of different varieties of English; - be able to analyse and compare different varieties of English from a linguistic viewpoint;  - analyse and evaluate their coursemates' presentations and essays and provide constructive feedback; - develop their analytical skills and oral and written expression skills.
